By Scott Yanow &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.allmusic.com/album/right-before-your-very-ears-mw0000673744&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.allmusic.com/album/right-before-your-very-ears-mw0000673744&lt;/a&gt;

After the rather violent opener (&quot;Run for Cover&quot;), one might be forgiven for
thinking that this trio outing by saxophonist Michael Blake, bassist Ben
Allison, and drummer Jeff Ballard was going to be mostly avant-garde jazz and
free-form explorations. As the program progresses, it is difficult not to be
impressed by the variety that includes the very spiritual and peaceful
&quot;Mt. Harissa,&quot; Allison slapping his bass in an old-time style on &quot;Flip,&quot; the
free bop of &quot;All of This Is Yours,&quot; a knowledgeable reading of Thelonious
Monk's &quot;San Francisco Holiday,&quot; and a somewhat spacy rendition of &quot;Careless
Love.&quot; This set keeps one continually guessing and certainly never loses one's
attention. Recommended.

--

